-- Tampa Bay Lightning Overcome New York Rangers 4-3 in Overtime
-- B y   N a n c y   K e r c h e v a l
-- 2012-03-03T05:00:01Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-03/tampa-bay-lightning-overcome-new-york-rangers-4-3-in-overtime.html
Ryan Malone scored one minute, 58
seconds into overtime to give the  Tampa Bay Lightning  a 4-3
victory over the Eastern Conference-leading New York Rangers,
who had their three-game winning streak ended.  The Rangers, 41-15-7 for 89 points, are one point behind
the National Hockey League-leading  Vancouver Canucks  and tied
for second with the  Detroit Red Wings .  Artem Anisimov gave the Rangers a 1-0 lead in the first
period at Tampa Bay Times Forum. Marian Gaborik added a power-
play goal two minutes, 43 seconds into the second period for a
2-0 lead.  Tom Pyatt narrowed the gap to 2-1 in second period, while
Teddy Purcell and Steven Stamkos gave the Lightning (30-28-6, 66
points) a 3-2 lead midway through the final period.  Brandon Dubinsky’s goal with 3 ½ minutes left in regulation
play tied the game at 3-3.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Nancy Kercheval in Washington at 
 nkercheval@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
